üî• Most Important StringBuilder Methods
1Ô∏è‚É£ append()
Adds text at the end.

StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder("Hello");
sb.append(" World");  // Hello World

2Ô∏è‚É£ insert()
Inserts text at a specific index.

sb.insert(5, " Java");  // Hello Java World

3Ô∏è‚É£ replace()
Replaces part of the string between start and end index.

sb.replace(0, 5, "Hi");  // Hi Java World

4Ô∏è‚É£ delete()
Deletes characters between start and end.

sb.delete(3, 8);  // Hi rld  (depending on previous state)

5Ô∏è‚É£ deleteCharAt()
Deletes a single character at given index.

sb.deleteCharAt(2);

6Ô∏è‚É£ reverse()
Reverses the entire string.

sb.reverse();

7Ô∏è‚É£ capacity()
Returns the current storage capacity.

int cap = sb.capacity();

8Ô∏è‚É£ length()
Returns the number of characters.

int len = sb.length();

9Ô∏è‚É£ charAt()
Returns character at specific index.

char c = sb.charAt(1);

üîü setCharAt()
Modifies a character at index.

sb.setCharAt(0, 'H');

1Ô∏è‚É£1Ô∏è‚É£ toString()
Converts StringBuilder back to String.

String str = sb.toString();

‚≠ê Quick Summary Table
Method	        Purpose
append()	    Add text at end
insert()	    Add text at a position
replace()	    Replace characters between indices
delete()	    Remove characters between indices
deleteCharAt()	Remove a single char
reverse()	    Reverse characters
capacity()	    Internal memory size
length()	    Current character count
charAt()	    Get character
setCharAt()	    Set character
toString()	    Convert to String